% drills.abc — LH and RH practice drills for lever harp hymn arrangement
% Style drills (#1-6): 8-bar demonstrations through the 7 church modes via a trefoil path.
% Pattern variations (#7+): 4-bar examples on a I-IV-V-I progression in C.
% Compile:  abcm2ps drills.abc -O drills.ps && ps2pdf drills.ps drills.pdf

%%titlefont Georgia 12 bold
%%subtitlefont Georgia 8 italic
%%composerfont Georgia 7 italic
%%pagenumbers 0
%%topmargin 0.6cm
%%botmargin 0.6cm
%%leftmargin 1cm
%%rightmargin 1cm
%%musicspace 0.15cm
%%maxshrink 0.9

% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
% STYLE DRILLS — 8-bar trefoil path, LH (bass clef)
% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
%   HARP DAMPING — legend used throughout this file
% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
%   ✓       No damping required — natural decay covers the transition
%   ⊕       Damp previous chord's strings at the bar line (palm-damp LH,
%           finger-damp RH) before striking the next bar's chord
%   ⊕⊕      Active damping throughout — scalar/stepwise/chromatic motion
%           piles adjacent strings into clusters; damp each note a fraction
%           before striking the next (or choose a different drill for
%           legato passages)
%
%   Each drill title includes a bracketed tag showing its damping demand.
%   In the staff, ⊕ symbols above the staff mark bar lines where
%   damping is required.
% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

X:1
T:1. Chorale  —  4ths CW, block 135 whole-note
C:Fingering 1·2·3 simultaneously
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=72
K:C clef=bass
"C""_8" [C,E,G,]4 | "F""_8" [F,A,C]4 | "B°""_8" [B,DF]4 | "Em""_8" [E,G,B,]4 | "Am""_8" [A,CE]4 | "Dm""_8" [D,F,A,]4 | "G""_8" [G,B,D]4 | "C""_8" [C,E,G,]4 |]

X:2
T:2. Rolled  —  2nds CW, 1358 quarter arpeggio
C:Fingering 1 2 3 4 ascending
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=100
K:C clef=bass
"C""_8" C, E, G, C | "Dm""_8" D, F, A, D | "Em""_8" E, G, B, E | "F""_8" F, A, C F | "G""_8" G, B, D G | "Am""_8" A, C E A | "B°""_8" B, D F B | "C""_8" C, E, G, C |]

X:3
T:3. Gospel Walk  —  4ths CCW, stride root/5th
C:Fingering 1 (root) then 2 (5th), damp between
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=112
K:C clef=bass
"C""_8" C, z G, z | "G""_8" G,, z D, z | "Dm""_8" D, z A, z | "Am""_8" A,, z E, z | "Em""_8" E, z B, z | "B°""_8" B,, z F, z | "F""_8" F, z C z | "C""_8" C, z G, z |]

X:4
T:4. Celtic Drone  —  2nds CCW, 15 dyad held (6/8)
C:Fingering 1·2 together, rings whole bar
M:6/8
L:1/8
Q:3/8=60
K:C clef=bass
"C""_8" [C,G,]6 | "B°""_8" [B,,F,]6 | "Am""_8" [A,,E,]6 | "G""_8" [G,,D,]6 | "F""_8" [F,C]6 | "Em""_8" [E,B,]6 | "Dm""_8" [D,A,]6 | "C""_8" [C,G,]6 |]

X:5
T:5. Praise Ballad  —  3rds CW, 135 arpeggio + rest
C:Fingering 1 2 3
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=70
K:C clef=bass
"C""_8" C, E, G, z | "Em""_8" E, G, B, z | "G""_8" G, B, D z | "B°""_8" B, D F z | "Dm""_8" D, F, A, z | "F""_8" F, A, C z | "Am""_8" A, C E z | "C""_8" C, E, G, z |]

X:6
T:6. Spiritual  —  3rds CCW, bass-and-chord stride
C:Fingering 1 (bass) b1+b3, 2·3·4 (chord stab) b2+b4
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=84
K:C clef=bass
"C""_8" C, [E,G,C] C, [E,G,C] | "Am""_8" A, [CEA] A, [CEA] | "F""_8" F, [A,CF] F, [A,CF] | "Dm""_8" D, [F,A,D] D, [F,A,D] | "B°""_8" B, [DFB] B, [DFB] | "G""_8" G, [B,DG] G, [B,DG] | "Em""_8" E, [G,B,E] E, [G,B,E] | "C""_8" C, [E,G,C] C, [E,G,C] |]

