% drills_grandstaff.abc — Grand-staff two-hand practice drills for hymn arrangement
% Drills #81-90: RH (treble) and LH (bass) interlocking on grand staff
% Compile:  abcm2ps drills_grandstaff.abc -O drills_grandstaff.ps && ps2pdf drills_grandstaff.ps drills_grandstaff.pdf

%%titlefont Georgia 12 bold
%%subtitlefont Georgia 8 italic
%%composerfont Georgia 7 italic
%%pagenumbers 0
%%topmargin 0.6cm
%%botmargin 0.6cm
%%leftmargin 1cm
%%rightmargin 1cm
%%musicspace 0.15cm
%%maxshrink 0.9

% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
% RH POCKET PATTERNS (#81-90)
% Patterns to play with the RH when you're NOT carrying the melody —
% intros, interludes, fills, atmospheric support.
% Each drill: RH pattern + simple whole-note LH anchor on the root.
% Trefoil = I-IV-V-I (4-bar demonstration in C).
% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

X:81
T:81. RH Pocket: Sustained Bed
T:Use when LH is busy — ring a chord over the groove
C:RH 1358 whole-note chord; LH simple root
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=80
%%score {V1 V2}
V:V1 clef=treble
V:V2 clef=bass
K:C
[V:V1] "C" [cegc']4 | "F" [fac'f']4 | "G" [gbd'g']4 | "C" [cegc']4 |]
[V:V2] C,4 | F,4 | G,4 | C,4 |]

X:82
T:82. RH Pocket: Pulse Stabs
T:Use when matching LH groove — rhythmic chord hits
C:RH chord quarter-note stabs; LH whole-note anchor
M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=96
%%score {V1 V2}
V:V1 clef=treble
V:V2 clef=bass
K:C
[V:V1] "C" [cegc'] [cegc'] [cegc'] [cegc'] | "F" [fac'f'] [fac'f'] [fac'f'] [fac'f'] | "G" [gbd'g'] [gbd'g'] [gbd'g'] [gbd'g'] | "C" [cegc'] [cegc'] [cegc'] [cegc'] |]
[V:V2] C,4 | F,4 | G,4 | C,4 |]

X:83
T:83. RH Pocket: Upward Arpeggio
T:Use to fill gaps between LH beats — flowing upward
C:RH ascending 1358 eighths; LH root anchor
M:4/4
L:1/8
Q:1/4=100
%%score {V1 V2}
V:V1 clef=treble
V:V2 clef=bass
K:C
[V:V1] "C" c e g c' c e g c' | "F" f a c' f' f a c' f' | "G" g b d' g' g b d' g' | "C" c e g c' c e g c' |]
[V:V2] C,8 | F,8 | G,8 | C,8 |]

X:84
T:84. RH Pocket: Tremolo Shimmer
T:Use for atmosphere — continuous high-register alternation
C:RH two chord tones alternating as sixteenths; LH anchor
M:4/4
L:1/16
Q:1/4=76
